Fun Banking Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 12/24/2023

Introduction
Welcome to Fun Banking, the interactive online banking simulator. Our commitment to your privacy is paramount. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, protect, and share information in relation to our website and services.

Information Collection
Personal Information: When you register, we collect information such as your email address, username, and password.

Simulated Banking Data: While using Fun Banking, any data entered such as simulated bank names, customer profiles, and financial transactions are stored.

Usage Data: We automatically collect information on how you interact with our services, like IP addresses, device information, and browser types.

Use of Information
Service Provision: Your information is used to personalize and improve your experience, manage your account, and provide customer support.

Analysis and Improvement: We analyze usage data to enhance our service offerings and user experience.

Legal Compliance: If necessary, we may use your information to comply with legal obligations.

Sharing of Information
With Consent: We may share your information with third parties when we have your explicit consent.
Service Providers: We may share information with third-party vendors who help us operate our services.
Legal Requirements: If required by law, we may disclose your information in response to legal processes.

Data Security
We implement robust security measures to protect against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction of your personal information and data stored on our platform.

Children's Privacy
Fun Banking is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.

Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.

Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at bytebury@gmail.com
